The World Health Organisation (WHO) sounded a rare global alarm declaring the DR Congo's Ebola outbreak an international emergency. It's only the fifth disease epidemic to have been given that status. Since the outbreak 11 months ago, 1 700 people have died. WHO has previously said hundreds of millions of dollars are needed to prevent it from spreading. Congo Ebola outbreak, a global health emergency Ebola outbreak in Congo declared international health emergency after more than 1,600 deaths. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 